Overstretched healthcare workers say Gauteng is not ready to deal with a second wave of COVID-19 infections. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Overstretched healthcare workers say Gauteng is not ready to deal with a second wave of COVID-19 infections. The province is among four areas in the country that have been flagged as hotspots. READ: Enforcing COVID-19 regulations in Buffalo City Over 5,000 people have died, and over 200,000 have been infected in Gauteng. But authorities say the situation is stable for now. eNCA reporter Manqoba Mchunu shares more details in the above.